Title: Simon-Vostre  ROUSE ILLUM 14
Relation.isPartOf: Richard H. and Mary A. Rouse Collection of Manuscripts. (Collection 360). Library Special Collections, Charles E. Young Research Library, University of California, Los Angeles.
Description.note: See H. Winger, LibraryQuarterly  for a picture and description of Vostre’s device. Regarding Vostre see Renouard, Repertoire, 431-432 and  R.H. & M.A. Rouse, Manuscripts and their Makers.  2. 135; for Pigouchet 2. 109.|~|Recto: Vostre’s  2/3 page printer’s images of a tree bearing a shield with the initials SV entwined, supported by two leopards gardant and the name SIMON VOSTRE in capitals on a scroll forming the lower border. ¾ frame in gold. Blue sky, green tree with brown trunk all brushed with gold.  Wood cut boarder stamps. Colophon, “impresse fuerint Parisius opera ac arte Nicolai hygmam. Impensis honesti viri Symonis Vostre: commorantis ibidem in vico novo. In inter sinio sancti Johannis evangelista.”  Verso: Table for finding moveable feasts.
